commentary: Mohammad Irfan to Guptill, OUT caught at long leg! The bouncer rises quickly on Guptill, who pulls but top edges it. The ball swirls high in the air towards long leg, where Wahab Riaz runs forward and to his left to judge the catch superbly. It was a lot like the chance Rahat Ali famously dropped off Wahab himself in the World Cup quarterfinal, giving Shane Watson a reprieve.

commentary: Mohammad Amir to Latham, OUT An appeal for caught behind is turned down and Pakistan are going to review the not out decision. Amir sent down another sharp bouncer that rose rapidly on Latham, who was trying to hook from his crease. There is no conclusive deviation, though it looks like one. Hot Spot doesn't show anything as the ball whizzes past the glove. There is a blip on the real time snicko though. Pakistan were super confident of their appeal. The third umpire decides that the spike on real time snicko is enough to overturn the decision. Latham has to go.
shortText: Mohammad Amir to Latham, OUT
text: An appeal for caught behind is turned down and Pakistan are going to review the not out decision. Amir sent down another sharp bouncer that rose rapidly on Latham, who was trying to hook from his crease. There is no conclusive deviation, though it looks like one. Hot Spot doesn't show anything as the ball whizzes past the glove. There is a blip on the real time snicko though. Pakistan were super confident of their appeal. The third umpire decides that the spike on real time snicko is enough to overturn the decision. Latham has to go.

commentary: Anwar Ali to McClenaghan, no run oh no, oh no, McClenaghan has been smashed in the face by a short ball after he missed the pull. The ball flew through the gap between the peak of the helmet and the grille and smashed into the region near his eye. The force was so much that the ball rebounded on to the grille off his face. That back padding of the helmet has been dislodged and is lying on the pitch. The crowd cheers as McClenaghan gets off his feet and begins to walk off the ground, there's a small swelling already.

commentary: Santner to Babar Azam, no run slides on outside off with extra bounce, Azam skips back and top-edges a cut to short third man. Sarfraz searches for a single, but is sent back. He tumbles, drops his bat on the floor, in the middle of the pitch. Sarfraz then recovers, dives desperately, and makes his ground, despite getting hit by the ball. Along the way, did he change his line, blocking the throw? Guptill and KW get together and have a chat with the umpire. Guptill was quite animated while KW was as cool as ever. Appeal for obstructing the throw? Sarfraz just got up after tumbling, did not disturb the throw... He just fell over to the other side of the pitch and then ran in a dead-straight line
